<title type="html"><![CDATA[A husband fulfilling his wife's needs..]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forum.salafiri.com/viewtopic.php?t=216&amp;p=223#p223"><![CDATA[
سئل شيخ الإسلام ابن تيمية رحمه الله:<br /><br />عن الرجل إذا صبر على زوجته الشهر والشهرين لا يطؤها فهل عليه إثم أم لا؟ وهل يطالب الزوج بذلك؟<br /><br />فأجاب:<br /><br />يجب على الرجل أن يطأ زوجته بالمعروف وهو من أوكد حقها عليه أعظم من إطعامها والوطء الواجب قيل: إنه واجب في كل أربعة أشهر مرة وقيل: بقدر حاجتها وقدرته كما يطعمها بقدر حاجتها وقدرته وهذا أصح القولين<br /><br /> مجموع الفتاوى لإبن تيمية 271/32<br /><br />Shaykh al-Islām ibn Taymiyyah  رحمه الله was asked about a man who stayed away from his wife for a month or two (months) and did not have sexual intercourse with her, is there any sin upon him and could he do such?<br /><br />He رحمه الله replied:<br /><br />The husband is obligated to have sexual intercourse with his wife on a reasonable basis, this is one of the most important rights that she has over him, it is more important than feeding her. It is said, that which is obligatory with regards to sexual intercourse is once every four months, or according to her needs and his ability, just as he should feed her according to her needs and his ability. <br /><br />Majmū al-Fatāwa ibn Taymiyyah 32/271 <br /><br />Translated by Authentic Quotes on Facebook<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forum.salafiri.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=63">Abu Faatimah</a> — Wed Aug 31, 2016 3:45 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
